{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888777931,"sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b37821b00106C6UGi7RJ6Opo","messageID":"msg_d7b374713001YU4fKBt5E54sPc","sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Overview\nThis document describes the delta specification for implementing the `publish` command in the AgentCube CLI.\n\n## Current State\n- The CLI framework exists with command structure\n- The `pack` command (AR-020) creates distributable archives\n- No publish functionality exists yet\n\n## Target State\nA fully functional `publish` command that:\n- Uploads packaged agents to the AgentCube registry\n- Handles authentication securely\n- Provides upload progress feedback\n- Validates packages before publishing\n\n## Delta Analysis\n\n### New Components\n1. **Publish Command Module** (`cmd/cli/publish.py`)\n   - CLI interface for publish command\n   - Argument parsing and validation\n   - Integration with upload logic\n\n2. **Registry Client** (`cmd/cli/internal/registry.py`)\n   - HTTP client for registry API\n   - Authentication handling\n   - Upload request construction\n\n3. **Authentication Module** (`cmd/cli/internal/auth.py`)\n   - API key/token management\n   - Credential storage and retrieval\n\n### Modified Components\n- `cmd/cli/main.py` - Add publish subcommand\n\n### Dependencies\n- Requires AR-020 (pack command) for package creation\n- Uses existing CLI framework\n\n## Interface Specification\n\n### Command Signature\n```bash\nagentcube publish [OPTIONS] <package-file>\n```\n\n### Options\n- `--registry, -r`: Target registry URL (default: https://registry.agentcube.io)\n- `--api-key, -k`: API key for authentication\n- `--dry-run`: Validate without uploading\n- `--verbose, -v`: Verbose output\n\n### Exit Codes\n- `0`: Success\n- `1`: General error\n- `2`: Authentication failed\n- `3`: Package validation failed\n- `4`: Upload failed\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Follow existing CLI patterns from other commands\n- Use streaming upload for large packages\n- Implement exponential backoff for retries\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775888777908,"end":1775888777930}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888777933,"sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b37b3650016Vbm2d9cfcThQD","messageID":"msg_d7b374713001YU4fKBt5E54sPc","sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/plan.md","content":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation\n- [ ] Set up command structure in `cmd/cli/publish.py`\n- [ ] Add publish subcommand to main CLI\n- [ ] Implement basic argument parsing\n\n## Phase 2: Authentication\n- [ ] Design authentication module\n- [ ] Implement API key storage/retrieval\n- [ ] Add authentication header generation\n\n## Phase 3: Registry Client\n- [ ] Create registry HTTP client\n- [ ] Implement upload endpoint\n- [ ] Add progress callback support\n\n## Phase 4: Package Validation\n- [ ] Validate package file exists and is readable\n- [ ] Verify package format\n- [ ] Check package metadata\n\n## Phase 5: Integration\n- [ ] Wire command to registry client\n- [ ] Implement dry-run mode\n- [ ] Add error handling and reporting\n\n## Phase 6: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for authentication module\n- [ ] Unit tests for registry client\n- [ ] Integration tests for publish command\n- [ ] Test error scenarios\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/plan.md","time":{"start":1775888777910,"end":1775888777932}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888777934,"sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b37d0d7001J75pmTIBzQFrjm","messageID":"msg_d7b374713001YU4fKBt5E54sPc","sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","content":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Design Document\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  CLI Interface  │\n│  (publish.py)   │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│  Auth Manager   │\n│   (auth.py)     │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│ Registry Client │\n│ (registry.py)   │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │ HTTP\n    ┌────▼────┐\n    │ Registry │\n    │  Server  │\n    └─────────┘\n```\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n### Authentication\n- API keys stored in `~/.agentcube/credentials`\n- Support for environment variable `AGENTCUBE_API_KEY`\n- Token refresh mechanism for session-based auth\n\n### Upload Strategy\n- Streaming upload to handle large packages\n- Chunked transfer for resumable uploads\n- Progress callback for CLI feedback\n\n### Error Handling\n- Structured error responses from registry\n- Retry logic for transient failures\n- Clear error messages for users\n\n## Data Flow\n1. Parse command arguments\n2. Load authentication credentials\n3. Validate package file\n4. Initialize upload request\n5. Stream package data\n6. Handle response\n7. Report result\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775888777913,"end":1775888777933}}}}
