{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888778301,"sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b37572f001VnFU3eN1VDrtPk","messageID":"msg_d7b374713001YU4fKBt5E54sPc","sessionID":"ses_284c9343cffeiZFXI2p5Yhu5Cq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/spec.yaml","content":"id: AR-022\ntitle: CLI publish 命令\nmodule: cmd/cli\nlanguage: Python\nsize: L\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n# Module: cmd/cli\n# Language: Python\n# Size: L\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: cli-command\n  description: |\n    Implement the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI. This command uploads\n    a packaged agent to the AgentCube registry, making it available for deployment\n    and sharing with other users.\n\n# Scope\nscope:\n  in:\n    - cmd/cli/publish command implementation\n    - Authentication with registry\n    - Package upload with progress\n    - Version management\n    - Metadata validation\n    - Registry response handling\n    - Success/failure reporting\n  out:\n    - Registry backend implementation\n    - Package build process (handled by pack command)\n    - User account management\n    - Organization/team features\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\nacceptance:\n  - Publish command uploads package to registry\n  - Supports authentication via API key or token\n  - Validates package before upload\n  - Shows upload progress\n  - Handles registry errors gracefully\n  - Returns proper exit codes\n  - Supports dry-run mode\n\n# References\nreferences:\n  - https://docs.python.org/3/library/urllib.request.html\n  - https://docs.python.org/3/library/http.client.html\n\n# Estimation\nestimation:\n  size: L\n  story_points: 8\n  days: 5\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"